Password Security Validator

Finn is helping Mama & Papa set up secure systems for all their new parenting accounts, like the login for the baby monitor and login for thier new diaper subscription. He needs to ensure all passwords meet proper security standards to keep everything safe. ðŸ”’


Given a password string, evaluate its strength and return "weak", "medium", or "strong" based on how many security rules it meets.


The security rules are:

At least 8 characters long
Contains both uppercase and lowercase letters
Contains at least one number
Contains at least one special character: !, @, #, %, ^, &, *

Scoring:

Weak: Fewer than 2 rules met
Medium: 2 or 3 rules met
Strong: All 4 rules met

Example 1:

Input: "Baby123"
Output: "weak"


**Explanation**: Only meets 2 rules (length âŒ, uppercase âœ…, lowercase âœ…, numbers âœ…, special âŒ)



Example 2:

Input: "SafeNursery2024"
Output: "medium"


**Explanation**: Meets 3 rules (length âœ…, uppercase âœ…, lowercase âœ…, numbers âœ…, special âŒ)



Example 3:

Input: "WelcomeBaby!2024"
Output: "strong"


**Explanation**: Meets all 4 rules (length âœ…, uppercase âœ…, lowercase âœ…, numbers âœ…, special âœ…)



Example 4:

Input: "abc"
Output: "weak"


**Explanation**: Only meets 1 rule (length âŒ, uppercase âŒ, lowercase âœ…, numbers âŒ, special âŒ)



Example 5:

Input: "Password!"
Output: "medium"


**Explanation**: Meets 3 rules (length âœ…, uppercase âœ…, lowercase âœ…, numbers âŒ, special âœ…)



Notes:

The password may contain any characters
Special characters are limited to: !, @, #, $, %, ^, &, *
Empty string should return "weak"
Evaluation is case-sensitive
////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
/*Do not change the name of the class or the method signature.*/
class Solution {
    public String evaluatePasswordStrength(String password) {
        // Your solution here
        Integer score =0;
        String specialChar ='[!@#%^&*]';
        Pattern numCheck =Pattern.compile('[0-9]');
        Boolean numCheck2 =numCheck.matcher(password).find();
        Pattern upperCase =Pattern.compile('[A-Z]');
        Boolean upperCase2 =upperCase.matcher(password).find();
        Pattern lowerCase =Pattern.compile('[a-z]');
        Boolean lowerCase2 =lowerCase.matcher(password).find();
        String strength;
        if(password.length() >=8)
        score =1+score;
        if(upperCase2 && lowerCase2)
        score =1+score;
        if(password.containsAny(specialChar))
        score =1+score;
        if(numCheck2)
        score =1+score;
        if(score <2)
        strength ='Weak';
        else if(score ==4)
        strength ='Strong';
        else
        strength ='Medium';
        return strength;
    }
}
